<DOCUMENT source-infobase-name="Rules" content-collection-id="NYCrules" source-infobase-title="The Rules of the City of New York" base-output-dir="D:\process\NFOProcess\codes\ny\newyorkcity\NYCrules\output\HUCCVLERTKEUARDR\" default-split-level="Chapter" makefile-filename="D:\process\NFOProcess\codes\ny\newyorkcity\NYCrules\output\HUCCVLERTKEUARDR\NYCrules.mak" css-stylesheet-href="#!-- #ID=NYCrules_css_id --#" xml-output-dir="D:\process\NFOProcess\codes\ny\newyorkcity\NYCrules\output\HUCCVLERTKEUARDR\XML\" css-stylesheet-name="NYCrules_css" makefile-document-depth="2">
	<LEVEL style-name="Chapter" style-name-escaped="Chapter" style-id="0-0-0-477" level-depth="2" toc-section="false">
		<RECORD id="0-0-0-83846" number="98502" version="3">
			<HEADING>Chapter 5: Rules Applicable to Violations of Laws or Regulations Enforced by the Taxi and Limousine Commission</HEADING>
			<PARA>
				<DESTINATION id="0-0-0-8531" name="T48C005"/>Chapter 5: Rules Applicable to Violations of Laws or Regulations Enforced by the Taxi and Limousine Commission</PARA>
		</RECORD>
		<LEVEL style-name="Normal Level" style-name-escaped="Normal-Level" style-id="0-0-0-0" level-depth="0" toc-section="false">
			<RECORD id="0-0-0-83847" number="98503" version="91">
				<PARA style-name="EdNoteSm" style-name-escaped="EdNoteSm" style-id="0-0-0-20">
					<CHARFORMAT bold="1" italic="0" underline="0" strike-out="0" hidden="0">Editor&apos;s note:</CHARFORMAT> Pursuant to City Record 7/8/2016, effective 8/7/2016, the Office of Administrative Trials and Hearings repealed and reenacted this chapter. <HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">[ALP S-004]</HIGHLIGHTER>
				</PARA>
			</RECORD>
		</LEVEL>
		<LEVEL style-name="Subchapter" style-name-escaped="Subchapter" style-id="0-0-0-480" level-depth="3" toc-section="false">
			<LEVEL style-name="Subtitle" style-name-escaped="Subtitle" style-id="0-0-0-15301" level-depth="4" toc-section="false">
				<LEVEL style-name="Part" style-name-escaped="Part" style-id="0-0-0-483" level-depth="5" toc-section="false">
					<LEVEL style-name="Subpart" style-name-escaped="Subpart" style-id="0-0-0-15960" level-depth="6" toc-section="false">
						<LEVEL style-name="Section" style-name-escaped="Section" style-id="0-0-0-486" level-depth="7" toc-section="true">
							<RECORD id="0-0-0-83848" number="98504" version="3">
								<HEADING>§ 5-01 Scope of this Chapter.</HEADING>
								<PARA>
									<DESTINATION id="0-0-0-11507" name="T48C005_5-01"/>§ 5-01 Scope of<CHARFORMAT bold="1" italic="0" underline="0" strike-out="0" hidden="0"> this Chapter.</CHARFORMAT>
								</PARA>
							</RECORD>
							<LEVEL style-name="Normal Level" style-name-escaped="Normal-Level" style-id="0-0-0-0" level-depth="0" toc-section="false">
								<RECORD id="0-0-0-83849" number="98505" version="1897">
									<PARA>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>This chapter applies to all charges of violations of any laws, rules and regulations enforced by the Taxi and Limousine Commission (TLC). Adjudications of such charges are conducted pursuant to the rules in 48 RCNY <LINK style-name="Jump" style-name-escaped="Jump" style-id="0-0-0-31" type="Jump" destination-name="T48C006" destination-id="0-0-0-11519">Chapter 6</LINK>. Where there is a conflict between this chapter and Chapter 6, this chapter takes precedence. Definitions in 48 RCNY § <LINK style-name="Jump" style-name-escaped="Jump" style-id="0-0-0-31" type="Jump" destination-name="T48C006_6-01" destination-id="0-0-0-11521">6-01</LINK> apply to terms used in this chapter. <HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">[ALP S-004]</HIGHLIGHTER>
									</PARA>
								</RECORD>
								<RECORD id="0-0-0-83851" number="98506" version="138">
									<PARA>(Added City Record 7/8/2016, eff. 8/7/2016) <HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">[ALP S-004]</HIGHLIGHTER>
									</PARA>
								</RECORD>
							</LEVEL>
						</LEVEL>
						<LEVEL style-name="Section" style-name-escaped="Section" style-id="0-0-0-486" level-depth="7" toc-section="true">
							<RECORD id="0-0-0-98010" number="98507" version="1537">
								<HEADING>§ 5-01a Appearances</HEADING>
								<PARA>
									<DESTINATION id="0-0-0-16202" name="T48C005_5-01a"/>§ 5-01a Appearances</PARA>
							</RECORD>
							<LEVEL style-name="Normal Level" style-name-escaped="Normal-Level" style-id="0-0-0-0" level-depth="0" toc-section="false">
								<RECORD id="0-0-0-119764" number="98508" version="2497">
									<PARA>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>(a)<TAB tab-count="1"/>
										<CHARFORMAT bold="0" italic="1" underline="0" strike-out="0" hidden="0">Appearances by Respondent.</CHARFORMAT> A Respondent&apos;s appearance at a hearing is timely if the Respondent appears and is ready to proceed no more than ninety (90) minutes after the scheduled hearing time. <HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">[ALP S-039]</HIGHLIGHTER>
									</PARA>
								</RECORD>
								<RECORD id="0-0-0-119765" number="98509" version="1537">
									<PARA>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>(b)<TAB tab-count="1"/>
										<CHARFORMAT bold="0" italic="1" underline="0" strike-out="0" hidden="0">Appearances by Petitioner.</CHARFORMAT> If the Petitioner fails to appear within thirty (30) minutes of the timely appearance of the Respondent and does not make a timely request to reschedule the hearing pursuant to 48 RCNY § <LINK style-name="Jump" style-name-escaped="Jump" style-id="0-0-0-31" type="Jump" destination-name="T48C006_6-05" destination-id="0-0-0-11531">6-05</LINK>, the Tribunal will dismiss the summons. <HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">[ALP S-039]</HIGHLIGHTER>
									</PARA>
								</RECORD>
								<RECORD id="0-0-0-119766" number="98510" version="1537">
									<PARA>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>(c)<TAB tab-count="1"/>If the hearing does not begin within three (3) hours of the timely appearance of both the Respondent and the Petitioner, the Tribunal will dismiss the summons without prejudice. <HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">[ALP S-039]</HIGHLIGHTER>
									</PARA>
								</RECORD>
								<RECORD id="0-0-0-119767" number="98511" version="1537">
									<PARA>(Added City Record 6/19/2019, eff. 7/19/2019) <HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">[ALP S-039]</HIGHLIGHTER>
									</PARA>
								</RECORD>
							</LEVEL>
						</LEVEL>
						<LEVEL style-name="Section" style-name-escaped="Section" style-id="0-0-0-486" level-depth="7" toc-section="true">
							<RECORD id="0-0-0-119768" number="98512" version="1537">
								<HEADING>§ 5-02 Respondent&apos;s Right to Confront Complaining Witness</HEADING>
								<PARA>
									<DESTINATION id="0-0-0-11509" name="T48C005_5-02"/>§ 5-02 Respondent&apos;s Right to Confront Complaining Witness</PARA>
							</RECORD>
							<LEVEL style-name="Normal Level" style-name-escaped="Normal-Level" style-id="0-0-0-0" level-depth="0" toc-section="false">
								<RECORD id="0-0-0-83852" number="98513" version="2102">
									<PARA>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>(a)<TAB tab-count="1"/>Pursuant to Administrative Code § <LINK style-name="Jump" style-name-escaped="Jump" style-id="0-0-0-31" type="Inter Infobase Jump" destination-infobase-id="671734137-329684122-0-0" destination-infobase-uil="L:\NY\New York City\Folio\Working\Admin.nfo" destination-infobase-name="" destination-infobase-title="" destination-name="19-506.1" destination-id="0-0-0-0">19-506.1</LINK>, the TLC must produce the complaining witness in person or by remote means where such witness&apos;s credibility is relevant to the summons being adjudicated. <HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">[ALP S-066]</HIGHLIGHTER>
									</PARA>
								</RECORD>
								<RECORD id="0-0-0-83853" number="98514" version="3">
									<PARA>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>(b)<TAB tab-count="1"/>If the TLC is unable to produce the witness in person or by videoconference or teleconference, it must provide the Hearing Officer with a statement outlining its efforts to produce the witness. If the Hearing Officer determines that the TLC&apos;s efforts were inadequate, the Hearing Officer will dismiss the summons. <HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">[ALP S-004]</HIGHLIGHTER>
									</PARA>
								</RECORD>
								<RECORD id="0-0-0-83854" number="98515" version="2102">
									<PARA>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>(c)<TAB tab-count="1"/>If the Respondent previously requested an adjournment to obtain the testimony of the complaining witness, the non-attendance of the complaining witness, either in person or by remote means, will be considered a failure by the TLC to produce a complaining witness under paragraph (b) and may be grounds for the Hearing Officer to dismiss the summons. <HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">[ALP S-066]</HIGHLIGHTER>
									</PARA>
								</RECORD>
								<RECORD id="0-0-0-83856" number="98516" version="2102">
									<PARA>(Added City Record 7/8/2016, eff. 8/7/2016; amended City Record 10/13/2021, eff. 10/13/2021) <HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">[ALP S-066]</HIGHLIGHTER>
									</PARA>
								</RECORD>
							</LEVEL>
						</LEVEL>
						<LEVEL style-name="Section" style-name-escaped="Section" style-id="0-0-0-486" level-depth="7" toc-section="true">
							<RECORD id="0-0-0-98011" number="98517" version="138">
								<HEADING>§ 5-03 Respondent&apos;s Right to Challenge a Default Decision</HEADING>
								<PARA>
									<DESTINATION id="0-0-0-11511" name="T48C005_5-03"/>§ 5-03 Respondent&apos;s Right to Challenge a Default Decision</PARA>
							</RECORD>
							<LEVEL style-name="Normal Level" style-name-escaped="Normal-Level" style-id="0-0-0-0" level-depth="0" toc-section="false">
								<RECORD id="0-0-0-83857" number="98518" version="1883">
									<PARA>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>Pursuant to Administrative Code § <LINK style-name="Jump" style-name-escaped="Jump" style-id="0-0-0-31" type="Inter Infobase Jump" destination-infobase-id="671734137-329684122-0-0" destination-infobase-uil="L:\NY\New York City\Folio\Working\Admin.nfo" destination-infobase-name="" destination-infobase-title="" destination-name="19-506.1" destination-id="0-0-0-0">19-506.1</LINK>, a Respondent may move to vacate a default decision by filing a written motion to vacate within two (2) years from the date of entry of the default decision. <HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">[ALP S-004]</HIGHLIGHTER>
									</PARA>
								</RECORD>
								<RECORD id="0-0-0-83859" number="98519" version="138">
									<PARA>(Added City Record 7/8/2016, eff. 8/7/2016) <HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">[ALP S-004]</HIGHLIGHTER>
									</PARA>
								</RECORD>
							</LEVEL>
						</LEVEL>
						<LEVEL style-name="Section" style-name-escaped="Section" style-id="0-0-0-486" level-depth="7" toc-section="true">
							<RECORD id="0-0-0-98012" number="98520" version="138">
								<HEADING>§ 5-04 Appeals</HEADING>
								<PARA>
									<DESTINATION id="0-0-0-11513" name="T48C005_5-04"/>§ 5-04 Appeals</PARA>
							</RECORD>
							<LEVEL style-name="Normal Level" style-name-escaped="Normal-Level" style-id="0-0-0-0" level-depth="0" toc-section="false">
								<RECORD id="0-0-0-83860" number="98521" version="2497">
									<PARA>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>(a)<TAB tab-count="1"/>If a Hearing Officer issues a decision imposing a reduced penalty pursuant to 48 RCNY § <LINK style-name="Jump" style-name-escaped="Jump" style-id="0-0-0-31" type="Jump" destination-name="T48C005_5-06" destination-id="0-0-0-11517">5-06</LINK>(c), the party seeking to appeal the Hearing Officer&apos;s underlying decision must file an appeal with the Tribunal within fifty (50) days of the date of the decision.</PARA>
								</RECORD>
								<RECORD id="0-0-0-119770" number="98522" version="1883">
									<PARA>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>(b)<TAB tab-count="1"/>Pursuant to Administrative Code § <LINK style-name="Jump" style-name-escaped="Jump" style-id="0-0-0-31" type="Inter Infobase Jump" destination-infobase-id="671734137-329684122-0-0" destination-infobase-uil="L:\NY\New York City\Folio\Working\Admin.nfo" destination-infobase-name="" destination-infobase-title="" destination-name="19-506.1" destination-id="0-0-0-0">19-506.1</LINK>(c), a Respondent will not be required to pay the fines, penalties, or restitution imposed in the decision in order to file a timely appeal. <HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">[ALP S-039]</HIGHLIGHTER>
									</PARA>
								</RECORD>
								<RECORD id="0-0-0-111583" number="98523" version="1537">
									<PARA>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>(c)<TAB tab-count="1"/>
										<CHARFORMAT bold="0" italic="1" underline="0" strike-out="0" hidden="0">Expedited appeals.</CHARFORMAT> Either party may appeal a decision pursuant to 48 RCNY § <LINK style-name="Jump" style-name-escaped="Jump" style-id="0-0-0-31" type="Jump" destination-name="T48C006_6-19" destination-id="0-0-0-11523">6-19</LINK>. Where the appeal involves the suspension or revocation of a TLC-issued license, the Appeals Unit will issue an expedited decision. <HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">[ALP S-039]</HIGHLIGHTER>
									</PARA>
								</RECORD>
								<RECORD id="0-0-0-83861" number="98524" version="1537">
									<PARA>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>(d)<TAB tab-count="1"/>A party responding to a request for appeal where the appeal involves the suspension or revocation of a TLC-issued license must file the response with the Tribunal within seven (7) days after being served with the appeal. The responding party must also serve a copy of the response on the appealing party, and file proof of such service with the Tribunal. <HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">[ALP S-039]</HIGHLIGHTER>
									</PARA>
								</RECORD>
								<RECORD id="0-0-0-83862" number="98525" version="1883">
									<PARA>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>(e)<TAB tab-count="1"/>
										<CHARFORMAT bold="0" italic="1" underline="0" strike-out="0" hidden="0">Requests for hearing recording.</CHARFORMAT> Pursuant to Administrative Code § <LINK style-name="Jump" style-name-escaped="Jump" style-id="0-0-0-31" type="Inter Infobase Jump" destination-infobase-id="671734137-329684122-0-0" destination-infobase-uil="L:\NY\New York City\Folio\Working\Admin.nfo" destination-infobase-name="" destination-infobase-title="" destination-name="19-506.1" destination-id="0-0-0-0">19-506.1</LINK>(d), if a Respondent appealing a decision requests in writing a copy of the hearing recording, the recording will be produced to the Respondent within thirty (30) days after receipt of the request. If the recording cannot be produced within the thirty (30) day period, the determination being appealed will be dismissed without prejudice. <HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">[ALP S-039]</HIGHLIGHTER>
									</PARA>
								</RECORD>
								<RECORD id="0-0-0-83863" number="98526" version="1537">
									<PARA>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>(g)<TAB tab-count="1"/>
										<CHARFORMAT bold="0" italic="1" underline="0" strike-out="0" hidden="0">Finality.</CHARFORMAT> A decision of the Appeals Unit becomes the final determination in the case, unless either party petitions the TLC Chairperson in accordance with § 35 RCNY <LINK style-name="Jump" style-name-escaped="Jump" style-id="0-0-0-31" type="Jump" destination-name="T35C068_68-12" destination-id="0-0-0-9605">68-12</LINK>(c). <HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">[ALP S-039]</HIGHLIGHTER>
									</PARA>
								</RECORD>
								<RECORD id="0-0-0-98013" number="98527" version="1537">
									<PARA>(Added City Record 7/8/2016, eff. 8/7/2016; amended City Record 12/5/2018, eff. 1/4/2019; amended City Record 6/19/2019, eff. 7/19/2019) <HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">[ALP S-039]</HIGHLIGHTER>
									</PARA>
								</RECORD>
							</LEVEL>
						</LEVEL>
						<LEVEL style-name="Section" style-name-escaped="Section" style-id="0-0-0-486" level-depth="7" toc-section="true">
							<RECORD id="0-0-0-119769" number="98528" version="1537">
								<HEADING>§ 5-05 Chairperson Review</HEADING>
								<PARA>
									<DESTINATION id="0-0-0-11515" name="T48C005_5-05"/>§ 5-05 Chairperson Review</PARA>
							</RECORD>
							<LEVEL style-name="Normal Level" style-name-escaped="Normal-Level" style-id="0-0-0-0" level-depth="0" toc-section="false">
								<RECORD id="0-0-0-83866" number="98529" version="1537">
									<PARA>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>(a)<TAB tab-count="1"/>
										<CHARFORMAT bold="0" italic="1" underline="0" strike-out="0" hidden="0">Scope of review of appeals unit decisions.</CHARFORMAT> The TLC Chairperson or, if designated by the TLC Chairperson, the General Counsel for the TLC, may review any determination of the Appeals Unit that interprets any of the following: <HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">[ALP S-039]</HIGHLIGHTER>
									</PARA>
								</RECORD>
								<RECORD id="0-0-0-83867" number="98530" version="1897">
									<PARA>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>(1)<TAB tab-count="1"/>A rule in <LINK style-name="Jump" style-name-escaped="Jump" style-id="0-0-0-31" type="Jump" destination-name="Title 35" destination-id="0-0-0-15524">Title 35</LINK> of the RCNY; <HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">[ALP S-004]</HIGHLIGHTER>
									</PARA>
								</RECORD>
								<RECORD id="0-0-0-83868" number="98531" version="1883">
									<PARA>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>(2)<TAB tab-count="1"/>A provision of law in <LINK style-name="Jump" style-name-escaped="Jump" style-id="0-0-0-31" type="Inter Infobase Jump" destination-infobase-id="671734137-329684122-0-0" destination-infobase-uil="L:\NY\New York City\Folio\Working\Admin.nfo" destination-infobase-name="" destination-infobase-title="" destination-name="T19C005" destination-id="0-0-0-0">Chapter 5 of Title 19</LINK> of the Administrative Code; <HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">[ALP S-004]</HIGHLIGHTER>
									</PARA>
								</RECORD>
								<RECORD id="0-0-0-83869" number="98532" version="1747">
									<PARA>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>(3)<TAB tab-count="1"/>A provision of law in <LINK style-name="Jump" style-name-escaped="Jump" style-id="0-0-0-31" type="Inter Infobase Jump" destination-infobase-id="1813066185-672468487-0-0" destination-infobase-uil="L:\NY\New York City\Folio\Working\Charter.NFO" destination-infobase-name="" destination-infobase-title="" destination-name="Chapter 65" destination-id="0-0-0-0">Chapter 65</LINK> of the Charter. <HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">[ALP S-004]</HIGHLIGHTER>
									</PARA>
								</RECORD>
								<RECORD id="0-0-0-83870" number="98533" version="3">
									<PARA>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>(b)<TAB tab-count="1"/>
										<CHARFORMAT bold="0" italic="1" underline="0" strike-out="0" hidden="0">Decision.</CHARFORMAT> Upon review, the TLC Chairperson or General Counsel may issue a decision adopting, rejecting or modifying the Appeals Unit decision. The TLC Chairperson or General Counsel will be bound by the findings of fact in the record and will set forth his or her decision in a written order. The TLC Chairperson or General Counsel&apos;s interpretation of the TLC&apos;s rules and the laws it administers will be considered agency policy and must be applied by the Tribunal in future adjudications involving the same rules or statutes. <HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">[ALP S-004]</HIGHLIGHTER>
									</PARA>
								</RECORD>
								<RECORD id="0-0-0-83872" number="98534" version="1537">
									<PARA>(Added City Record 7/8/2016, eff. 8/7/2016; amended City Record 6/19/2019, eff. 7/19/2019) <HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">[ALP S-039]</HIGHLIGHTER>
									</PARA>
								</RECORD>
							</LEVEL>
						</LEVEL>
						<LEVEL style-name="Section" style-name-escaped="Section" style-id="0-0-0-486" level-depth="7" toc-section="true">
							<RECORD id="0-0-0-98014" number="98535" version="1537">
								<HEADING>§ 5-06 Special Procedures</HEADING>
								<PARA>
									<DESTINATION id="0-0-0-11517" name="T48C005_5-06"/>§ 5-06 Special Procedures</PARA>
							</RECORD>
							<LEVEL style-name="Normal Level" style-name-escaped="Normal-Level" style-id="0-0-0-0" level-depth="0" toc-section="false">
								<RECORD id="0-0-0-83873" number="98536" version="1537">
									<PARA>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>(a)<TAB tab-count="1"/>
										<CHARFORMAT bold="0" italic="1" underline="0" strike-out="0" hidden="0">Summary suspension based on a failure to be timely tested for drug use.</CHARFORMAT> When the TLC submits to the Tribunal written documentation pursuant to 35 RCNY § <LINK style-name="Jump" style-name-escaped="Jump" style-id="0-0-0-31" type="Jump" destination-name="T35C068_68-16" destination-id="0-0-0-9611">68-16</LINK>(d) submitted by a Licensee, as defined in 35 RCNY § <LINK style-name="Jump" style-name-escaped="Jump" style-id="0-0-0-31" type="Jump" destination-name="T35C051_51-03" destination-id="0-0-0-8521">51-03</LINK>, refuting summary suspension based on a failure to be timely tested for drug use, the Tribunal will issue a decision based on the written documentation. The decision will include findings of fact and conclusions of law. The decision may be appealed in accordance with the process established in 48 RCNY § <LINK style-name="Jump" style-name-escaped="Jump" style-id="0-0-0-31" type="Jump" destination-name="T48C006_6-19" destination-id="0-0-0-11523">6-19</LINK>. <HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">[ALP S-004]</HIGHLIGHTER>
									</PARA>
								</RECORD>
								<RECORD id="0-0-0-83874" number="98537" version="1883">
									<PARA>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>(b)<TAB tab-count="1"/>
										<CHARFORMAT bold="0" italic="1" underline="0" strike-out="0" hidden="0">Unlicensed activity.</CHARFORMAT> Pursuant to § <LINK style-name="Jump" style-name-escaped="Jump" style-id="0-0-0-31" type="Inter Infobase Jump" destination-infobase-id="671734137-329684122-0-0" destination-infobase-uil="L:\NY\New York City\Folio\Working\Admin.nfo" destination-infobase-name="" destination-infobase-title="" destination-name="19-529.2" destination-id="0-0-0-0">19-529.2</LINK> of the Administrative Code, a decision on unlicensed activity with a commuter van will be issued within one (1) business day of the conclusion of the hearing or the default. <HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">[ALP S-004]</HIGHLIGHTER>
									</PARA>
								</RECORD>
								<RECORD id="0-0-0-83876" number="98538" version="1537">
									<PARA>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>(c)<TAB tab-count="1"/>
										<CHARFORMAT bold="0" italic="1" underline="0" strike-out="0" hidden="0">Discretion of Hearing Officers to reduce penalties.</CHARFORMAT>&#160;<HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">[ALP S-039]</HIGHLIGHTER>
									</PARA>
								</RECORD>
								<RECORD id="0-0-0-119783" number="98539" version="1883">
									<PARA>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>(1)<TAB tab-count="1"/>A Hearing Officer may, in the interest of justice, impose a reduced penalty for a violation, except for a violation of § <LINK style-name="Jump" style-name-escaped="Jump" style-id="0-0-0-31" type="Inter Infobase Jump" destination-infobase-id="671734137-329684122-0-0" destination-infobase-uil="L:\NY\New York City\Folio\Working\Admin.nfo" destination-infobase-name="" destination-infobase-title="" destination-name="19-507" destination-id="0-0-0-0">19-507</LINK> of the Administrative Code, after determining that such reduction in penalty is appropriate on the ground that one or more compelling considerations or circumstances clearly demonstrates that imposing such penalty would constitute or result in injustice. In determining whether such compelling consideration or circumstance exists, the Hearing Officer must, to the extent applicable, consider, individually and collectively, the following factors: <HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">[ALP S-039]</HIGHLIGHTER>
									</PARA>
								</RECORD>
								<RECORD id="0-0-0-119784" number="98540" version="1537">
									<PARA>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>(i)<TAB tab-count="1"/>The seriousness and circumstances of the violation; <HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">[ALP S-039]</HIGHLIGHTER>
									</PARA>
								</RECORD>
								<RECORD id="0-0-0-119782" number="98541" version="1537">
									<PARA>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>(ii)<TAB tab-count="1"/>The extent of harm caused by the violation; <HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">[ALP S-039]</HIGHLIGHTER>
									</PARA>
								</RECORD>
								<RECORD id="0-0-0-119781" number="98542" version="1537">
									<PARA>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>(iii)<TAB tab-count="1"/>The evidence supporting or refuting the violation charged, whether admissible or inadmissible at a hearing; <HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">[ALP S-039]</HIGHLIGHTER>
									</PARA>
								</RECORD>
								<RECORD id="0-0-0-119780" number="98543" version="1537">
									<PARA>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>(iv)<TAB tab-count="1"/>The history, character, and condition of the Respondent; <HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">[ALP S-039]</HIGHLIGHTER>
									</PARA>
								</RECORD>
								<RECORD id="0-0-0-119779" number="98544" version="1537">
									<PARA>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>(v)<TAB tab-count="1"/>The effect of imposing upon the Respondent the penalty set by the TLC; <HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">[ALP S-039]</HIGHLIGHTER>
									</PARA>
								</RECORD>
								<RECORD id="0-0-0-119778" number="98545" version="1537">
									<PARA>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>(vi)<TAB tab-count="1"/>The impact of a penalty reduction on the safety or welfare of the community; <HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">[ALP S-039]</HIGHLIGHTER>
									</PARA>
								</RECORD>
								<RECORD id="0-0-0-119777" number="98546" version="1537">
									<PARA>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>(vii)<TAB tab-count="1"/>The impact of a penalty reduction on public confidence in the TLC, the Tribunal, and the implementation of laws by the City; <HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">[ALP S-039]</HIGHLIGHTER>
									</PARA>
								</RECORD>
								<RECORD id="0-0-0-119776" number="98547" version="1537">
									<PARA>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>(viii)<TAB tab-count="1"/>The position of the Petitioner regarding the proposed fine reduction with reference to the specific circumstances of the Respondent and the violation charged; and <HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">[ALP S-039]</HIGHLIGHTER>
									</PARA>
								</RECORD>
								<RECORD id="0-0-0-119775" number="98548" version="1537">
									<PARA>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>(ix)<TAB tab-count="1"/>Any other relevant fact indicating whether a decision to impose the penalty set by the TLC on the Respondent would serve a useful purpose. <HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">[ALP S-039]</HIGHLIGHTER>
									</PARA>
								</RECORD>
								<RECORD id="0-0-0-119774" number="98549" version="1537">
									<PARA>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>(2)<TAB tab-count="1"/>Upon determining that a penalty should be reduced, the Hearing Officer will set forth in the decision the monetary penalty, if any, to be imposed on the Respondent, the amount of the reduction, and the reasons for such reduction. <HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">[ALP S-039]</HIGHLIGHTER>
									</PARA>
								</RECORD>
								<RECORD id="0-0-0-119773" number="98550" version="1537">
									<PARA>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>(3)<TAB tab-count="1"/>Within twenty (20) business days of receipt of the Hearing Officer&apos;s decision, the TLC Chairperson or the Chairperson&apos;s designee may, upon determining that such decision is not in the interest of justice, pursuant to the factors set forth in Paragraph (1) of this subdivision, re-impose the full penalty demanded by the TLC or increase the penalty imposed by the Hearing Officer. <HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">[ALP S-039]</HIGHLIGHTER>
									</PARA>
								</RECORD>
								<RECORD id="0-0-0-119771" number="98551" version="1537">
									<PARA>(Added City Record 7/8/2016, eff. 8/7/2016; amended City Record 6/19/2019, eff. 7/19/2019) <HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">[ALP S-039]</HIGHLIGHTER>
									</PARA>
								</RECORD>
							</LEVEL>
						</LEVEL>
					</LEVEL>
				</LEVEL>
			</LEVEL>
		</LEVEL>
	</LEVEL>
</DOCUMENT>